NAME
    update_bulk - bulk update records from JSON array

SYNOPSIS
    update_bulk <model> [--file=<file>] [--dry-run]
    cat data.json | update_bulk <model>

DESCRIPTION
    Updates multiple records efficiently using a single API call.
    Input must be a JSON array of record objects with "id" fields.

    Unlike update, this command:
    - Does NOT accept field=value pairs
    - Requires JSON array input with "id" in each object
    - Uses direct API for better performance
    - Is designed for batch operations

OPTIONS
    --file=<path>
        Read JSON from file instead of stdin.

    --dry-run
        Validate input without updating. Reports how many
        records would be updated.

EXAMPLES
    cat users.json | update_bulk users
        Bulk update from piped JSON

    update_bulk products --file=products.json
        Update from file

    update_bulk orders --dry-run < orders.json
        Validate without updating

INPUT FORMAT
    Input must be a JSON array of objects with "id" fields:

    [
      {"id": "abc-123", "status": "active"},
      {"id": "def-456", "role": "admin"}
    ]

    Only specified fields are updated; others remain unchanged.

OUTPUT
    On success: "Updated N records in <model>"
    On dry-run: "Dry run: would update N records in <model>"

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success
    1   Error (invalid JSON, missing IDs, API error, etc.)

SEE ALSO
    update, insert_bulk, delete_bulk, select
